      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "## What's new in 1.0.3\n\n### Fix: \"Link to Google Drive folder\" no longer disappears before sign-in\n\nThe **Link to Google Drive folder** option was only shown after completing Google OAuth sign-in. Since linking only stores a folder ID and a local-folder mapping (no files are transferred), it's now available as soon as Google Drive credentials are configured — you can link a folder first and sign in later before your first upload/download.\n\n- **Link to Google Drive folder** now requires only that Drive credentials are configured.\n- **Upload to Google Drive as new folder** still requires an active connection, since it transfers files immediately.\n- Download / Upload / Unlink behaviour for already-linked projects is unchanged.\n\n### Internal: tighter vault enumeration\n\n- The folder picker now reads Obsidian's in-memory index instead of walking the whole vault tree.\n- The note picker excludes files already in the project, so it only lists genuinely addable notes.",
      "downloadCount": 32,
      "draft": false,
      "name": "1.0.3",
      "prerelease": false,
      "publishedAt": "2026-05-29T11:16:56Z",
