      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "## What's new in 1.0.2\n\n### Google Drive — link, unlink, and upload as new folder\n\nThree new actions are available in the project context menu (both the project list and the content pane ⋮ menu) when Google Drive is connected in plugin settings.\n\n**For projects not yet linked to Drive:**\n\n- **Link to Google Drive folder** — paste a Drive folder share link or ID to associate it with the project. Pick the vault folder whose contents map to that Drive folder. No files are transferred. Once linked, the existing Upload / Download actions become available.\n- **Upload to Google Drive as new folder** — creates a brand-new Drive folder named after the project under a chosen parent (or My Drive root) and uploads the project's local folder into it in one step. The project is automatically linked to the new folder afterwards.\n\n**For projects already linked to Drive:**\n\n- **Unlink from Google Drive** — removes the Drive association from the project. Local files and Drive files are left completely untouched. A confirmation prompt is shown before unlinking.\n\nThe menu adapts automatically: link/upload-as-new are shown only when the project is unlinked; download/upload/unlink are shown only when a Drive folder is linked.\n\n### CSS quality\n\nRemoved all `!important` declarations from `styles.css` — each override is now expressed through higher selector specificity instead, making the styles easier for themes to customise.",
